name: S&P 500
description: Tracks 500 of the largest publicly traded companies in the U.S.

name: Dow Jones Industrial Average
description: Tracks 30 large well-established 'blue-chip' U.S. companies.

name: Nasdaq Composite
description: Tracks all stocks listed on the Nasdaq exchange known for being tech-heavy.

name: Nasdaq 100
description: Tracks the 100 largest non-financial companies listed on the Nasdaq.

name: Russell 2000
description: Tracks 2000 small-capitalization U.S. companies.

name: CBOE Volatility Index
description: Measures the market's expectation of 30-day volatility; the 'Fear Index'.

name: S&P 400 MidCap
description: Tracks 400 mid-sized U.S. companies.

name: Russell 1000
description: Tracks the 1000 largest U.S. companies.

name: Russell 3000
description: Tracks 3000 of the largest U.S. stocks representing about 98% of the market.

name: NYSE Composite
description: Tracks all common stocks listed on the New York Stock Exchange.

name: Dow Jones Transportation Average
description: Tracks 20 leading U.S. transportation stocks (airlines railroads etc.).

name: Dow Jones Utility Average
description: Tracks 15 prominent U.S. utility companies.

name: PHLX Semiconductor Sector Index
description: Tracks 30 of the largest companies involved in semiconductor design and manufacturing.

name: Nasdaq Biotechnology Index
description: Tracks Nasdaq-listed biotechnology and pharmaceutical companies.

name: KBW Bank Index
description: Tracks 24 of the largest U.S. banking institutions.

name: S&P 100
description: Represents a sub-set of the S&P 500 tracking 100 of the largest blue-chip companies.

name: PHLX Gold/Silver Sector Index
description: Tracks companies involved in the gold and silver mining industry.

name: NYSE Arca Gold BUGS Index
description: Tracks companies involved in gold mining that do not hedge their gold production.

name: NYSE Arca Airline Index
description: A benchmark for the performance of major U.S. and overseas airlines.

name: S&P 500 Information Technology
description: Tracks the technology companies within the S&P 500.

name: S&P 500 Health Care
description: Tracks the health care companies within the S&P 500.

name: S&P 500 Financials
description: Tracks the financial companies within the S&P 500.

name: S&P 500 Consumer Discretionary
description: Tracks consumer discretionary companies within the S&P 500.

name: S&P 500 Industrials
description: Tracks the industrial companies within the S&P 500.

name: S&P 500 Consumer Staples
description: Tracks consumer staples companies within the S&P 500.

name: S&P 500 Utilities
description: Tracks the utility companies within the S&P 500.

name: S&P 500 Materials
description: Tracks the materials companies within the S&P 500.

name: S&P 500 Real Estate
description: Tracks the real estate companies (mostly REITs) within the S&P 500.

name: S&P 500 Communication Services
description: Tracks communication services companies within the S&P 500.

name: Russell 1000 Growth
description: Tracks Russell 1000 companies with higher growth metrics.

name: Russell 1000 Value
description: Tracks Russell 1000 companies with value characteristics.

name: Russell 2000 Growth
description: Tracks Russell 2000 companies with higher growth potential.

name: Russell 2000 Value
description: Tracks Russell 2000 companies with value characteristics.

name: S&P 500 Equal Weight Index
description: An equal-weighted version of the S&P 500 where all companies have the same influence.

name: Dow Jones U.S. Total Stock Market Index
description: A very broad index designed to track the entire U.S. stock market.

name: Dow Jones US Financials Index
description: A broad measure of the U.S. financials sector.

name: S&P High Yield Dividend Aristocrats
description: Tracks S&P 1500 companies that have increased dividends for 20+ consecutive years.

name: ICE BofA MOVE Index
description: Measures bond market volatility often seen as a counterpart to the VIX.

name: CBOE 10-Year Treasury Note Yield
description: Tracks the yield on the U.S. 10-Year Treasury note.

name: CBOE 30-Year Treasury Bond Yield
description: Tracks the yield on the U.S. 30-Year Treasury bond.

name: CBOE 13-Week Treasury Bill Yield
description: Tracks the yield on the 13-week U.S. Treasury bill.

name: NYSE Arca Oil Index
description: Tracks major companies involved in all phases of the oil industry.

name: NYSE Arca Pharmaceutical Index
description: A benchmark for the performance of major pharmaceutical companies.

name: Dow Jones FXCM Dollar Index
description: Tracks the value of the U.S. dollar against a basket of other major currencies.

name: CBOE SKEW Index
description: Measures the perceived risk of outlier returns (a 'black swan' event) in the S&P 500.

name: S&P GSCI
description: A benchmark for investment in the commodity markets.

name: Bloomberg Commodity Index
description: A broadly diversified commodity index distributed across various commodity sectors.

name: NYSE Arca Natural Gas Index
description: Tracks companies involved in the natural gas industry.

name: Wilshire 5000 Total Market Index
description: The broadest U.S. stock market index tracking thousands of companies.

name: Euro Stoxx 50
description: Tracks 50 of the largest and most liquid stocks in the Eurozone.

name: Nikkei 225
description: The leading price-weighted index for the Tokyo Stock Exchange.

name: FTSE 100
description: Tracks the 100 largest companies on the London Stock Exchange.

name: DAX PERFORMANCE-INDEX
description: Tracks 40 major German companies on the Frankfurt Stock Exchange.

name: CAC 40
description: Tracks the 40 largest French stocks on the Euronext Paris exchange.

name: Hang Seng Index
description: Tracks the largest companies on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange.

name: KOSPI Composite Index
description: Tracks all common stocks on the Korea Stock Exchange.

name: AEX-Index
description: Tracks the 25 most traded securities on the Euronext Amsterdam.

name: BEL 20
description: Tracks the 20 largest stocks on the Euronext Brussels.

name: Swiss Market Index
description: Tracks the 20 largest stocks on the SIX Swiss Exchange.

name: S&P/ASX 200
description: Tracks the 200 largest stocks on the Australian Securities Exchange.

name: IBOVESPA
description: The main performance indicator of the Brazil stock market.

name: IPC MEXICO
description: Tracks the 35 most liquid stocks on the Mexican Stock Exchange.

name: S&P/TSX Composite Index
description: The headline index for the Canadian equity market.

name: MERVAL
description: The most important index of the Buenos Aires Stock Exchange.

name: Jakarta Composite Index
description: The main stock market index in Indonesia.

name: FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI
description: Tracks the 30 largest companies on the Bursa Malaysia.

name: S&P/NZX 50 Index
description: The main stock market index in New Zealand.

name: Straits Times Index
description: Tracks the top 30 companies on the Singapore Exchange.

name: TSEC weighted index
description: The main stock market index in Taiwan.
